==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rapprochement
<hw>Rap`proche`ment"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>rapprocher</ets> to cause to approach again. See <er>Re-</er>;
<er>Approach</er>.]</ety> <def>Act or fact of coming or being drawn near
or together; establishment or state of cordial relations.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><q>He had witnessed the gradual <qex>rapprochement</qex> between the
papacy and Austria.</q> <rj><qau>Wilfrid Ward.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rapscallion</ent>⟦br⟧
